00:37:52,186 --> 00:37:53,729
ASSHOLE GOD
FUCKING CHRIST

530
00:38:06,450 --> 00:38:08,703
So we want to know

531
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:13,624
where all the money went
when it should be in one place.

532
00:38:14,875 --> 00:38:17,128
Did Father Baek really take it?

533
00:38:17,628 --> 00:38:19,714
Can you see how ridiculous this is?

534
00:38:20,506 --> 00:38:21,465
Father.

535
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:23,426
I apologize.

536
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:27,221
We should have held
the memorial Mass at the church.

537
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:29,307
-I'm really sorry.
-No, it's fine.

538
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:34,812
Is Sister Chae-hwan not coming?

539
00:38:35,688 --> 00:38:38,607
No, she's not.
She seemed ill, so I told her to rest.

540
00:38:39,108 --> 00:38:40,276
And the fire

541
00:38:41,694 --> 00:38:43,696
was caused by a short circuit.

542
00:38:45,239 --> 00:38:47,158
Well, the building is old.

543
00:38:49,994 --> 00:38:50,828
Father.

544
00:38:51,579 --> 00:38:54,165
About the voice incident yesterday,

545
00:38:55,458 --> 00:38:56,584
do you have any leads?

546
00:38:57,168 --> 00:38:58,002
I'm not sure.

547
00:38:59,587 --> 00:39:01,088
But first, as a priest,

548
00:39:01,839 --> 00:39:06,093
I believe the issues raised by the voice
should not be overlooked.

549
00:39:07,386 --> 00:39:08,554
Yes, that's right.

550
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:12,183
We must confirm whether it's true or not.

551
00:39:12,266 --> 00:39:13,100
I mean,

552
00:39:14,268 --> 00:39:17,188
the culprit must know something about it.

553
00:39:17,271 --> 00:39:18,689
If we catch the culprit--

554
00:39:18,773 --> 00:39:22,860
To ruin such a meaningful Mass
is blasphemy against the Holy Spirit.

555
00:39:22,943 --> 00:39:25,696
A grave offense according to Canon Law.

556
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:26,697
That's right.

557
00:39:26,781 --> 00:39:29,700
And your son took the time out
to attend with you.

558
00:39:30,284 --> 00:39:32,495
God, you're all so frustrating.

559
00:39:33,579 --> 00:39:37,333
That's not what matters right now.
We have to find the money!

560
00:39:40,294 --> 00:39:43,297
Well, put aside the money.

561
00:39:44,173 --> 00:39:46,884
The good faith of the believers
has gone up in smoke.

562
00:39:47,468 --> 00:39:49,970
Isn't that blasphemy
against the Holy Spirit?

563
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:53,474
We need to search and seize the ledgers
related to the funds and donations!

564
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:58,646
I keep thinking about Father Baek.
I can't help it.

565
00:40:06,737 --> 00:40:07,571
Good heavens!

566
00:40:07,655 --> 00:40:09,657
Shit, that scared me.

567
00:40:18,749 --> 00:40:22,086
I know this may sound random,

568
00:40:23,629 --> 00:40:26,715
but I think we should reinforce
the outer walls.

569
00:40:28,509 --> 00:40:33,180
We have less than 200 days left,
but to think we have to look at

570
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:37,518
these burnt and broken walls
during that whole time is a bit…

571
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:43,107
Even if we have only a day left to live,
we should still keep our stomachs full

572
00:40:43,190 --> 00:40:45,526
and keep our minds happy, no?

573
00:40:46,026 --> 00:40:47,153
On that note,

574
00:40:47,653 --> 00:40:51,240
I have some close plasterer friends
who aren't working these days,

575
00:40:51,323 --> 00:40:53,075
so I spoke to them about this.

576
00:40:54,076 --> 00:40:57,413
We're discussing an important issue here.
Let's talk about that later--

577
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:59,999
No. What she's saying is important too.

578
00:41:00,082 --> 00:41:04,170
That's right. I also feel uncomfortable
to see the church like this.

579
00:41:04,253 --> 00:41:06,130
I'll help too.

580
00:41:06,213 --> 00:41:07,047
Sure.

581
00:41:11,802 --> 00:41:14,638
Why stick your nose in their business?
You have no right!

582
00:41:14,722 --> 00:41:17,183
Think of all the money
we offered to the church!

583
00:41:17,266 --> 00:41:18,100
"We"?

584
00:41:18,726 --> 00:41:19,977
What do you mean "we"?

585
00:41:20,686 --> 00:41:23,272
With what conscience
would you meddle with church matters?

586
00:41:23,355 --> 00:41:25,441
Aren't you ashamed to face Ha-yul?

587
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:28,652
You embarrass me so much

588
00:41:28,736 --> 00:41:31,405
that I haven't been
anywhere near the church in ages.

589
00:41:31,906 --> 00:41:33,741
But things are different for Ha-yul.

590
00:41:33,824 --> 00:41:36,160
She has her friends and her teacher there.

591
00:41:36,243 --> 00:41:37,995
So it's all my fault again, huh?

592
00:41:38,579 --> 00:41:40,414
Fine, then let's just all die together.

593
00:41:40,498 --> 00:41:41,999
Stop calling the shots for us.

594
00:41:42,082 --> 00:41:44,293
Who do you think you are?
It's not the end yet.

595
00:41:44,376 --> 00:41:47,296
Be honest with me.
Why do you keep going to the church?

596
00:41:50,007 --> 00:41:53,594
You donated to the church behind my back
when Father Baek was around.

597
00:41:54,094 --> 00:41:57,181
He bought gold for himself with the money,
and that pisses me off!

598
00:41:59,099 --> 00:42:03,521
That money was from the account
my parents set up for me.

599
00:42:03,604 --> 00:42:05,439
-It wasn't yours!
-Does that matter?

600
00:42:06,106 --> 00:42:08,192
We have to find it whoever it belongs to!

601
00:42:09,443 --> 00:42:10,528
Enough with your…

602
00:42:29,713 --> 00:42:30,881
Hey, teammate?

603
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:39,223
What's wrong?

604
00:42:42,059 --> 00:42:45,312
Oh dear, that's becoming a habit, really.

605
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:48,816
I guess it's because
Min-ho's birthday is coming up.

606
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:51,569
Yeah?

607
00:42:57,324 --> 00:42:58,701
I know how you'd feel.

608
00:43:03,163 --> 00:43:07,001
By the way, there was a meeting
at the church today.

609
00:43:08,419 --> 00:43:10,671
That man, Ha-yul's father, was there too.

610
00:43:11,171 --> 00:43:16,385
And he was shouting at Father Woo,
telling him to return the extension funds.

611
00:43:17,094 --> 00:43:21,348
He's just gone a bit crazy right now
because of money.

612
00:43:21,432 --> 00:43:24,893
He's not that special.
We're all going through the same thing.

613
00:43:25,603 --> 00:43:29,231
I, for one, want to just bang my head
against a wall and kill myself.

614
00:43:34,194 --> 00:43:36,030
Hey, cheer up, okay?

615
00:43:43,329 --> 00:43:44,747
-No.
-I'm scared!

616
00:43:44,830 --> 00:43:46,707
There was a fire at Cheondong Church.

617
00:43:47,958 --> 00:43:51,670
I was so upset
to see the church burned black.

618
00:43:53,422 --> 00:43:56,884
Auntie said she would fix the church
with some men.

619
00:44:01,221 --> 00:44:02,848
There are 188 days left.

620
00:44:03,891 --> 00:44:05,559
The days are counting down.

621
00:44:06,393 --> 00:44:09,897
Even scarier things will happen
when the asteroid comes, won't they?

622
00:44:12,858 --> 00:44:13,859
Woo-chan, help me!

623
00:44:15,486 --> 00:44:16,904
No!

624
00:44:18,822 --> 00:44:19,740
Help!

625
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:24,578
174 DAYS UNTIL ASTEROID COLLISION

626
00:44:26,372 --> 00:44:31,669
IN-A

627
00:44:31,752 --> 00:44:32,753
Hot.

628
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:08,122
Hello.

629
00:45:09,039 --> 00:45:10,040
That's right.

630
00:45:10,958 --> 00:45:12,459
You finally came out.

631
00:45:13,669 --> 00:45:14,586
There.

632
00:45:15,629 --> 00:45:17,381
So you're Choco.

633
00:45:21,009 --> 00:45:22,344
Gotcha.

634
00:45:39,653 --> 00:45:43,615
Regarding the recent assault,
we found that both parties were at fault.

635
00:45:45,826 --> 00:45:49,037
Show respect to your fellow soldiers,
or there will be no survival.

636
00:45:49,913 --> 00:45:54,084
If this kind of incident occurs again,
you will be punished by military law.

637
00:45:54,585 --> 00:45:57,337
It was Sergeant Kim again, right?

638
00:45:58,380 --> 00:46:01,049
That fucking moron.

639
00:46:03,552 --> 00:46:05,304
I'm gonna destroy him. Fuck.

640
00:46:08,015 --> 00:46:09,099
-Sir.
-Hey.

641
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:13,103
You're off guard duty for one month
and on cleaning and maintenance duty.

642
00:46:14,772 --> 00:46:16,523
But this was insubordination.

643
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:18,776
Why do I have to be treated
like I screwed up?

644
00:46:18,859 --> 00:46:20,194
Shut the hell up!

645
00:46:20,277 --> 00:46:22,780
You've got a big mouth
for someone who made a mess.

646
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:24,948
I can't do it.

647
00:46:25,783 --> 00:46:28,786
I may as well be discharged
if I'm gonna be the battalion lackey.

648
00:46:28,869 --> 00:46:30,996
What, you want to be discharged?

649
00:46:32,873 --> 00:46:35,626
Na Hyeon-jae will just
keep going out as a driver.

650
00:46:35,709 --> 00:46:36,585
No, he won't.

651
00:46:37,669 --> 00:46:38,504
What?

652
00:46:42,424 --> 00:46:43,342
Hi, Hyeon-jae.

653
00:46:45,594 --> 00:46:46,762
I asked for you.

654
00:46:48,764 --> 00:46:55,103
Our duty is to protect our honored guests
using every means possible.

655
00:46:55,187 --> 00:46:56,188
From whom?

656
00:46:56,688 --> 00:46:59,358
Anyone looking for a chance
to kidnap them.

657
00:47:00,275 --> 00:47:01,109
Hey, come here.

658
00:47:03,821 --> 00:47:04,822
Get over here!

659
00:47:05,322 --> 00:47:07,032
Put those down and come here.

660
00:47:07,699 --> 00:47:09,368
-I'm fine, ma'am.
-What do you mean?

661
00:47:09,868 --> 00:47:11,370
Are you disobeying an order?

662
00:47:11,995 --> 00:47:13,330
-No, ma'am.
-Put them down.

663
00:47:20,212 --> 00:47:23,215
You'll have to be on higher alert
than when you're on guard duty.

664
00:47:24,007 --> 00:47:25,008
Understood, ma'am.

665
00:47:26,343 --> 00:47:27,594
Aren't they so pretty?

666
00:47:31,765 --> 00:47:33,767
Hello, you're all here.

667
00:47:34,852 --> 00:47:35,686
Come.

668
00:47:38,605 --> 00:47:40,524
Yes. Get inside.

669
00:47:40,607 --> 00:47:43,777
If the outer walls are done,
wrap things up.

670
00:47:44,361 --> 00:47:45,946
Let's decide what we'll do inside.

671
00:47:49,783 --> 00:47:53,954
Those men are really skilled, aren't they?

672
00:47:54,037 --> 00:47:57,624
That's right.
In the North, they were special force--

673
00:47:58,458 --> 00:47:59,293
No.

674
00:47:59,793 --> 00:48:02,129
-They were special technicians.
-All right.

675
00:48:02,212 --> 00:48:03,297
Gye Hyang!

676
00:48:04,047 --> 00:48:06,049
Look at this. Good as new, huh?

677
00:48:06,133 --> 00:48:09,344
Just as I expected!
No wonder you get paid so much.

678
00:48:09,428 --> 00:48:11,430
Wait, you're going to pay me?

679
00:48:11,513 --> 00:48:15,183
Think of it as volunteer work.
Show some faith to the Lord.

680
00:48:15,267 --> 00:48:18,103
Don't you think you should do
some good deeds before you die?

681
00:48:18,186 --> 00:48:19,938
Gye Hyang, look over here!

682
00:48:20,689 --> 00:48:24,276
These old tiles were hard to get,
so we're a bit short.

683
00:48:24,359 --> 00:48:26,695
Won't it look a bit patchy?

684
00:48:26,778 --> 00:48:29,531
Don't worry about it at all.

685
00:48:29,615 --> 00:48:31,825
It's way better than black soot.

686
00:48:31,909 --> 00:48:33,160
It looks great.

687
00:48:33,243 --> 00:48:35,954
-I got it. Don't worry.
-You said it yourself, okay?

688
00:48:36,455 --> 00:48:39,791
Right, I heard it's chaotic
in North Korea too.

689
00:48:41,001 --> 00:48:41,835
Yes.

690
00:48:42,669 --> 00:48:48,091
I was this close to saving up enough money
and bringing the rest of my family here.

691
00:48:48,175 --> 00:48:49,092
Yeah?

692
00:48:50,510 --> 00:48:51,637
Hold it right.

693
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:53,430
It's off-balance.

694
00:48:54,056 --> 00:48:56,808
I can't lift up my arms.
Let's just drag it.

695
00:49:00,938 --> 00:49:03,857
Sister Regina must be in great shock.

696
00:49:04,608 --> 00:49:06,109
Her face is all puffy.

697
00:49:10,864 --> 00:49:13,700
The church is her home,
and she saw it go up in flames.

698
00:49:13,784 --> 00:49:16,036
Sister, are you okay?

699
00:49:20,290 --> 00:49:24,044
People used to come here to take photos
because a famous architect designed it.

700
00:49:24,127 --> 00:49:25,462
Now it looks hideous.

701
00:49:26,964 --> 00:49:27,965
Come on!

702
00:49:28,715 --> 00:49:31,426
What's the point in all this scrubbing?

703
00:49:32,844 --> 00:49:35,514
Scrubbing won't fix
what's broken and twisted!

704
00:49:37,099 --> 00:49:39,434
Did it splash on you?

705
00:49:39,518 --> 00:49:40,435
My bad.

706
00:49:41,979 --> 00:49:43,063
You're still down?

707
00:49:43,689 --> 00:49:44,773
Sister!

708
00:49:46,233 --> 00:49:48,235
You should prepare the group meal.

709
00:49:48,318 --> 00:49:49,987
Don't act confused.

710
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:52,155
Go about your duties calmly
as you always have.

711
00:49:53,740 --> 00:49:55,575
Yes, go about my duties.

712
00:49:56,326 --> 00:49:58,161
Let's go!

713
00:50:05,252 --> 00:50:07,879
I mean, are you all right? You need this?

714
00:50:11,591 --> 00:50:13,844
I'll take care of this. Let me.

715
00:50:16,346 --> 00:50:18,849
The work just doesn't seem to end.

716
00:50:21,268 --> 00:50:23,020
Dear me!

717
00:50:23,520 --> 00:50:24,980
Bishop, this is Father Woo.

718
00:50:26,898 --> 00:50:27,733
Yes.

719
00:50:30,944 --> 00:50:32,612
We were told it was an accident.

720
00:50:35,240 --> 00:50:36,074
Yes.

721
00:50:38,577 --> 00:50:39,995
Yes, of course.

722
00:50:41,455 --> 00:50:42,289
Yes.

723
00:50:43,290 --> 00:50:47,627
Well, it wasn't arson, at least.

724
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:50,422
With all fire insurance suspended,

725
00:50:51,214 --> 00:50:53,258
it doesn't matter what caused the fire.

726
00:50:54,301 --> 00:50:57,471
From the look of things,
the diocese might help us out.

727
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:58,722
That's right.

728
00:50:58,805 --> 00:51:01,808
They won't turn a blind eye
just because Father Baek's not here.

729
00:51:01,892 --> 00:51:04,978
Do you think the diocese has
some kind of plan in place?

730
00:51:05,062 --> 00:51:05,896
Of course!

731
00:51:07,272 --> 00:51:09,024
I don't know what to think anymore.

732
00:51:38,637 --> 00:51:39,471
What you doin'?

733
00:51:40,097 --> 00:51:41,098
Is it over already?

734
00:51:41,181 --> 00:51:42,182
Yup.

735
00:51:46,520 --> 00:51:47,813
What did the diocese say?

736
00:51:49,523 --> 00:51:51,108
Father Baek isn't here.

737
00:51:53,276 --> 00:51:55,112
And there was a fire on top of that.

738
00:51:56,530 --> 00:51:57,823
Nothing at all.

739
00:51:59,783 --> 00:52:02,869
I guess they are leaving us on our own
since the end is near anyway.

740
00:52:04,037 --> 00:52:06,164
So I'm thinking about what to do.

741
00:52:07,958 --> 00:52:09,709
But you don't know a thing.

742
00:52:09,793 --> 00:52:12,295
And there's nothing you can do.

743
00:52:15,006 --> 00:52:18,510
Still, you looked badass for a second
when you told the investigator to leave.

744
00:52:18,593 --> 00:52:20,428
-I did?
-You did!

745
00:52:29,980 --> 00:52:31,356
Why did he disappear?

746
00:52:33,984 --> 00:52:35,485
And when we're so helpless.

747
00:52:37,154 --> 00:52:39,948
Remember what Father Baek used to say?

748
00:52:43,076 --> 00:52:44,911
Maybe we're on our way to maturity.

749
00:52:46,746 --> 00:52:48,331
That's even more confusing.

750
00:52:54,171 --> 00:52:56,840
Father, would you like to eat first?

751
00:52:56,923 --> 00:52:58,091
No, let's eat together.

752
00:52:58,175 --> 00:52:59,176
-Okay.
-Thank you.

753
00:53:36,129 --> 00:53:37,464
If I could,

754
00:53:39,299 --> 00:53:41,593
I would spend the days we have left

755
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:44,888
finding those scumbags…

756
00:53:47,474 --> 00:53:48,642
and punishing them.

757
00:53:50,268 --> 00:53:52,020
I don't expect forgiveness.

758
00:53:57,567 --> 00:53:58,777
With such ill thoughts…

759
00:54:01,238 --> 00:54:03,657
I won't be able to reunite
with Min-ho, will I?

760
00:54:11,748 --> 00:54:12,999
Sister Christina.

761
00:54:17,337 --> 00:54:18,672
"Vengeance is mine."

762
00:54:19,673 --> 00:54:21,508
"With vengeance, I will repay."

763
00:54:23,468 --> 00:54:25,387
Those were God's words.

764
00:54:48,285 --> 00:54:51,121
-I want sausage!
-Thank you for the grace you've given us.

765
00:54:51,204 --> 00:54:52,706
I want sausage!

766
00:54:52,789 --> 00:54:54,124
Amen.

767
00:54:54,207 --> 00:54:55,875
I want sausage!

768
00:54:55,959 --> 00:54:59,462
Goodness, the little pup must be hungry.

769
00:55:00,130 --> 00:55:02,716
-Thank you for the food. Enjoy.
-Thank you.

770
00:55:02,799 --> 00:55:04,801
-Drinks!
-Enjoy your meal.

771
00:55:04,884 --> 00:55:07,387
You all worked hard today,
so let's share a drink.

772
00:55:07,470 --> 00:55:08,513
Just one glass each.

773
00:55:09,973 --> 00:55:11,474
Where's Mi-ryeong?

774
00:55:11,558 --> 00:55:13,977
She said her stomach was upset.
She went home.

775
00:55:14,060 --> 00:55:15,520
She told me to have dinner here.

776
00:55:15,603 --> 00:55:17,689
What? Why doesn't she feel good?

777
00:55:17,772 --> 00:55:19,441
Not sure. She said it was churning.

778
00:55:19,941 --> 00:55:22,527
-But it's not good to skip meals.
-Eat up.

779
00:55:23,069 --> 00:55:24,904
She's stressed out, that's why.

780
00:55:26,573 --> 00:55:29,576
Father, about the Mass going forward…

781
00:56:18,375 --> 00:56:20,460
It's me. Se-kyung.

782
00:56:40,563 --> 00:56:41,648
Where did it all go?

783
00:56:42,399 --> 00:56:43,233
Where…

784
00:56:44,484 --> 00:56:46,194
We said we'd drink this together.

785
00:56:49,948 --> 00:56:50,949
What?

786
00:56:51,032 --> 00:56:55,036
I had only one thing on my mind
